commit.message: register custom lossy packet per packet ID
put new callback into aipdsl definition file
put custom callback function into C def section
fix the comment to make sense
allow to send all custom lossy packet IDs
convert 2 log warnings to debug. they seems to be useless and appear very often
allow saving of ToxAV object in toxcore
store ToxAV object in toxcore and retrieve in rtp.c
put the void* at the end of Tox struct, otherwise mono_time crashes somewhere
remove logging with msi (it's ToxAV stuff)
make it compile and pass most tests (still a bit hacky!!)

script to run asan compile locally in docker

fix more errors,
remove Messenger from RTPSession,
use toxav mono_time in rtp.c

add missing return() statement causing asan failures,
fix a comment and also make something a bit clearer

add own stackstraces,
NEVER EVER use this on any real tox instances!!
NEVER EVER ever
